{
  "texts": [
    "They use input attributes to make decisions, which can be output classes or numerical values.",
    "The tree structure involves arranging attributes based on data values, with the root at the top and nodes branching from it.",
    "Decisions are generated at the endpoints where no further splitting occurs (Alloghani et al., 2020).",
    "Hunt's algorithm drives the selection of sequences for each node, determining the order of decisions.",
    "The Gini impurity is introduced to achieve accurate classification based on these attributes, minimizing the Gini index to 0 (Plapinger, 2017)."
  ]
}